  "fdesetup_status": "FileVault is On.",
  "notes": [
    "Volume keybag location (apfs_keybag_loc in the volume superblock) is not exposed by diskutil. Reading it requires a raw read of the volume's checkpoint blocks, which is EX-28-blocked on the live data volume under SIP. A detached encrypted .dmg could be read raw, but we don't have one in the fixture set.",
    "diskutil's `Encryption: bool` reflects the on-disk fs_flags ~APFS_FS_UNENCRYPTED state. During an encryption rollover (FileVault being turned on for the first time, or a key rotation in progress) the EncryptionRollingState field is populated.",
    "Apple silicon Macs always have Data Protection on the data volume even if FileVault is off \u2014 the class keys are wrapped by Secure Enclave hardware keys. FileVault adds a user-password-derived wrapping layer on top."
  ],
